Description: CX - AI-powered package manager for Linux
 CX is an AI-powered package manager that understands natural language.
 It translates plain English commands into Linux operations, eliminating
 traditional documentation complexity.
 .
 Features:
  - Natural language package installation and management
  - Hardware-aware optimization with GPU detection
  - Security sandbox using Firejail and AppArmor
  - Multi-LLM support (Ollama, Claude, OpenAI)
  - Offline-capable operation with local LLMs
  - Smart dependency resolution
  - Configuration management
 .
 The cx CLI is installed to /usr/bin/cx. Configuration files
 are stored in /etc/cx/.
